<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="851" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.60 Manchuria/4–3046: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-30T17:00:00-04:00">April 30,
                                1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>12. Dept would appreciate such detailed info as may be available regarding
                        Russian seizure of Jap industrial enterprises Manchuria, especially
                        Anshan.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>